{
  "stem": "5430.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So even though we were dealing a lot with the Christian trade-- or Christian customers, but we were kosher.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I know many-- on many occasions an indigent person would come in and they would feed him and no charge.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was part of the tradition, you know?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And no poor person went out hungry from our place.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember mostly my own neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I really don't remember much of-- you know, it's-- when the war came, I was, what, 14, 15 years old?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And but most of the things that I remember is our own neighborhood, which is Leszno Street, [POLISH] around the-- we didn't venture out further away from the house.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the only thing I remember as far as incidents with my non-- non-Jewish friends was I relied a lot on my brothers to protect me.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we in our neighborhood had a very strong youth moment.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My brothers belonged to Betar and were self-protected.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Wherever they-- gangs would come in our neighborhood, you know, to beat up on Jews and all that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They would not succeed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were quite well organized.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "At one time, I recall-- I was still a youngster-- and a group of Christian guys came in to try to beat up on the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they organized it so that they let him come into our street.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they blocked off-- all the houses were built with main entrances in each building so that once you came into the street and each main doors for the buildings were closed, there were no ways of going out other than the beginning of the block or the end of the block.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And this one occasion stands out in my mind.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They, they got together and they blocked off the exit.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
